snippet: Dutch voters appeared to give Prime Minister Mark Rutte a narrow victory, which will relieve European allies anxious about rising euro skepticism in the richer countries of the north.
lead_paragraph: Dutch voters appeared to give Prime Minister Mark Rutte a narrow victory, which will relieve European allies anxious about rising euro skepticism in the richer countries of the north.
